Doctor schema - defines as a medical professional who can diagnose and treat patients
- firstName
- lastName
- email (unique)
- username (unique)
- password
- contactNumber
- specialty
- active (default: true)

Patient Schema: defines as an individual seeking medical care
- firstname
- lastname
- email (unique)
- username (unique)
- password
- contactNumber
- dateOfBirth
- medicalHistory
- active (default: true)

Appointment Schema: defines as a scheduled meeting between a doctor and a patient for medical consultation
- doctor (reference to Doctor)
- patient (reference to Patient)
- appointmentDate
- reason
- status (scheduled, completed, cancelled)

Diagnosis Schema: Diagnosis defined as a medical condition identified during an appointment
- appointment (reference to Appointment)
- diagnosisDetails
- prescribedTreatment
- followUpDate (optional)

Prescription Schema: defines as a medication order prescribed by a doctor for a patient based on a diagnosis
- diagnosis (reference to Diagnosis)
- medicationName
- dosage
- frequency
- duration
- notes (optional)